      },
      "date": "2017-09-28 03:31:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n\"I guess this bug didn't hit previously because we had smaller requests and always hit the OUT_UPDATE_INIT_BUFFER_SIZE check to increase the size to 4096?\"\n\nOh, for update log, the log header is 32k, so in our regular auto test, it will definitely generate update > 4k.\n\nThis problem is caused by o2ib driver in RHEL-7.4, see the comment in LU-9983.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
